CAN Diag Lib

Files

file  diagLib_can.h
 This file contains the prototypes of the APIs present in the software test library file of CAN. This also contains some related macros.

Detailed Description

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum DiagLib_CanReturnTypes

Enum to represent return types for CAN diaglib.

Enumerator
DIAGLIB_CAN_DATA_MISMATCH 

Data mismatch error

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_TIMEOUT 

The test has timedout

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_INVALID_PARAMS 

The test has failed due to invalid parameters

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_BADARGS 

The test has failed due to bad arguments

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_FAIL 

The test has failed in atleast one iteration

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_OK 

The test has passed in all iterations till now

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_PENDING 

The test is still running an iteration

DIAGLIB_CAN_PARITY_DBE_ISR_RECEIVED 

Double bit parity error event received

DIAGLIB_CAN_PARITY_SBE_ISR_RECEIVED 

Single bit parity error event received

DIAGLIB_CAN_LOOPBACK_VERIFIED 

Loopback test verified event received

enum DiagLib_CanTestTypes

Enum to select type of test for CAN.

Enumerator
DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_INT_LOOPBACK 

The test type internal loop-back

DIAGLIB_CAN_TEST_EXT_LOOPBACK 

The test type external loop-back

DIAGLIB_CAN_PARITY_ECC_TEST 

The test type Parity

int32_t DiagLib_canStartTest ( DiagLib_CanTestParam_t *  testPrm)

This API is used for CAN internal loop-back/parity test.

Parameters
testPrmPointer to structure DiagLib_CanTestParam_t.
Returns
status Test run status.
Note
For parity test a single bit error is introduced and corrected data is verified.
int32_t DiagLib_canTestParamsInit ( DiagLib_CanTestParam_t *  testPrm)

This API is used for initializing Can test parameters to default. This API has to be called from application before starting the test.

Parameters
testPrmPointer to structure DiagLib_CanTestParam_t.
Returns
None.
Note
parameters 'canModule' and 'testType' of structure DiagLib_CanTestParam_t must be initialized before calling this API.
